}

q {
Q:"Measure of the central angle of an arc of a circle whose length is equal to the radius of the circle is known as:"
A:"b"
O:a) "1 degree", b) "1 radian", c) "1 right angle", d) "1 reflex angle"
R:"This is the definition of a radian."
}

q {
Q:"A circular wire of radius 3cm is cut straightened and then bent so as to lie along the circumference of a hoop of radius 24cm. The measure of the angle subtended at the center of the hoop is:"
A:"c"
O:a) "15°", b) "30°", c) "45°", d) "60°"
R:"Arc length \\(s = 2\\pi(3) = 6\\pi\\). Angle \\(\\theta = s/R = 6\\pi/24 = \\pi/4\\) rad = \\(45^\\circ\\)."
}

q {
Q:"\\(\\sin 50^\\circ - \\sin 70^\\circ + \\sin 10^\\circ\\) is equal to:"
A:"b"
O:a) "-1", b) "0", c) "1", d) "2"
R:"\\(\\sin 50^\\circ + \\sin 10^\\circ = 2\\sin 30^\\circ \\cos 20^\\circ = \\cos 20^\\circ\\). Since \\(\\sin 70^\\circ = \\cos 20^\\circ\\), result is 0."
}

q {
Q:"The value of the expression \\(\\tan 10^\\circ \\tan 20^\\circ \\dots \\tan 89^\\circ\\) is equal to:"
A:"b"
O:a) "0", b) "1", c) "2", d) "3"
R:"Pairs like \\(\\tan \\theta\\) and \\(\\tan(90^\\circ - \\theta)\\) multiply to 1. \\(\\tan 45^\\circ = 1\\). The entire product is 1."
}

q {
